well another very long and busy day has come to an end we completed our final presentations of this epic tour today in pei and we finished with a bang this morning we visited colonel gray high school were we presented to two separate groups of students which i feel went very well as soon as the second presentation was over we had to hustle to our second school of the day stone park intermediate as soon as we arrived at the school i could tell right away that this was going to be a great school to finish our tour off with there was so much good energy here and that was certainly evident during and after the presentation i think my part of our final presentation was when one of the students asked when birthday was and we responded in a couple of weeks then without any prompting all  students in attendance starting singing happy birthday to afterwards we had a group photo everyone and we packed up and headed to studio for to do an interview for their news show compass this was an interview that did himself for the most part and i just stood back in awe thinking this would never of been possible a couple of years ago i think it was the best ones he has ever done once filming wrapped up we met up with some friends that we met a couple of years ago at the kart track in and they took us for the most amazing lobster dinner in downtown i have some video of tackling a lobster for the first time which has to be seen to be believed we have our final event tomorrow at east coast in and after that we will finally be homeward bound till then goodnight and god bless lincolnelectric autismawareness onelapatatime
